---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContentImage from '../../components/ContentImage.astro';
import toadproofBarrier from '../../assets/images/toadproof-fencing-barrier.png';
import toadproofInstall from '../../assets/images/toadproof-fencing-install.png';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Toad Proof Fencing: Best Barrier Strategies for Florida Homes"
  description="Toad proof fencing guide for South Florida homeowners. Learn where cane toad barriers work best and how fencing supports long-term bufo toad control."
>
  <div class="urgency">
    <strong>Important:</strong> Fencing helps prevention, but does not replace emergency care. See the <a href="/cane-toad-dog-poisoning/">dog poisoning guide</a> for urgent exposure.
  </div>

  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Toad Proof Fencing for Cane Toad Control</h1>
    <p>Toad proof fencing can reduce cane toad entry into high-risk zones like dog run areas, pool perimeters, and lanai access points when installed correctly.</p>
    <a href="/cane-toad-removal/" class="btn btn-lg">Get Local Fencing Guidance -></a>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h2>Where Toad-Proof Barriers Work Best</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Pool decks and lanai perimeters</li>
      <li>Pet relief and play zones</li>
      <li>Fence lines with known ground-level gaps</li>
    </ul>

    <figure class="content-figure">
      <ContentImage
        src={toadproofBarrier}
        alt="Mesh barrier along a Florida yard fence line to block cane toads from entering pet and pool areas"
      />
      <figcaption>Barriers work best when gaps at the bottom and along gates are minimized.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>Design Principles for Better Results</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Minimize ground clearance and edge gaps</li>
      <li>Inspect after heavy rain for erosion openings</li>
      <li>Pair barriers with habitat reduction and removal visits</li>
    </ul>

    <figure class="content-figure">
      <ContentImage
        src={toadproofInstall}
        alt="Installing a low toad-proof mesh barrier at ground level along a residential fence in South Florida"
      />
      <figcaption>Professional-style installs often combine rigid mesh with tight ground contact and periodic re-inspection after rain.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>What Fencing Cannot Do Alone</h2>
    <p>Barriers reduce entry but do not remove existing toads. Most homeowners get the best outcome by combining fencing with professional cane toad removal and property adjustments.</p>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details><summary>Is toad proof fencing enough by itself?</summary><p>Usually no. It is most effective when part of a layered control strategy.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Can fencing help protect dogs?</summary><p>Yes, especially when focused on pet zones and used with nighttime supervision.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Should fencing be installed before or after removal?</summary><p>Many homes benefit from initial removal first, then barrier upgrades to limit re-entry.</p></details>
    </div>

    <p>Already seeing toads? <a href="/cane-toad-removal/">Connect with a removal pro -></a></p>
    <p>More context: <a href="/cane-toad-florida/">Cane Toad Florida guide -></a>.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
